The general rule of accrual between co-legatees is tersely stated in the text, though there was some difference according to the form employed. lt they were conjoined re, ie. disiunctim‚ and one or more ol thern failed to take, the accrual operated ipso iure: there was no right ol refusal in those who took, and who consequently were unaliected by any fidei· commissa or other burdens imposed by the testator on those who had sailed: it they were conjoined re et verbis, they had the option ol re- fusing the shares ot' those who failed, or os taking them subject to such charges, Cod 6. 51. 11.
